text.text: Today I went to the bus stop and asked if there was a taxi available. They said there was a taxi, I said I would go close to G√ºlseren Pond. It took 35-40 minutes by walking and 5-7 minutes by taxi. The gentleman taxi driver, Ismet, said that Inonu Boulevard was closed, so he would take another route and it would cost around 180 TL. The chances of the road being closed were close to zero. I didn't believe what he said and walked the whole way and there wasn't even 1 meter of road that was closed. I am writing this so that these people, who lie without thinking and who do not like short distances, may feel ashamed when they read it. I think it should be our duty not to receive service from people with such immoral attitudes.
